org.sbml.jsbml.ext.fbc

Class Objective

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode
      • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractSBase
        • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractNamedSBase
          • org.sbml.jsbml.ext.fbc.Objective
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, NamedSBase, SBase, UniqueNamedSBase, UniqueSId, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    public class Objective
extends AbstractNamedSBase
implements UniqueNamedSBase
    An integral component in a complete description of a steady-state model is the so-called 'objective function' which generally consists of a linear combination of model variables (fluxes) and a sense (direction). In the FBC package this concept is succinctly captured in the Objective class.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Nicolas Rodriguez, Andreas Dräger
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
